McGill Training and Human Resources Development Project, McGill University, 2007 – 2008
I characterized the spatial relationship between health and social service providers and linguistic-minorities in Quebec. The project aimed to identify where services for English-speakers were lacking and to address this inequality through training. I co-presented research findings at two conferences, which in turn, gave me a chance to understand the value of discussion with specialists from different disciplines and fields of study.


